--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/apm.c
Shows your rough 'actions per minute', you want this to be a low
number if possible.  Otherwise bad things could happen.  To you.

Your 'commands per minute' represents commands you've entered during
active (non-idle/LD) time on your character.  The average over boot
(obviously) counts the whole boot whether you were around or not.

