file: /cmds/mortal/ask.c
keywords: mortal, communication, tell, converse, respond, talk, say, tellb
aliases: 
short:  Phrase a comment in the form of a question
header: Topic: Ask

  SYNTAX: ask <message>

The 'ask' and 'tell' commands are identical, but are both installed
for the grammatical convenience of the player.

These commands let you send a message to a single player on the
mud, whether they are in the room or not.  For high mortals, this
is without cost, but for everybody else, the cost is 5 spell points
per tell.

You cannot send a tell to anyone that is tellblocking you.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/auction.c
keywords: mortal, afind
aliases: 
short: Auction Line Commands
header: Topic: Auction
syntax: auction


Official Pinnacle Auction Line

Type 'auction' to get your own copy of the auction line.

Auction Commands:
  atalk    : talk on auction line (only during auction)
  abid     : bid on current auction item(s)
  acheck   : check the items and bid on the current auction
           : "acheck long" will show an items long description
  ablock   : block the auction line
  adestroy : destroy this auction line
  ahistory : lists the last bunch of auctions

-------------Auction House Commands---------------
  ahlist [filter] : Show items for sale at the auction house
  ahview <item>   : Show long desc for auction <item>
  ahhist [reverse]: Show recent auction history
                    <the above cost 50 coins to do remotely!>
  ahbid <#> <amt> : Bid from afar (costs 100 coins and not within
                    30 seconds of auction end.)

To auction items, you must go see the auctioneer down from Cancer.
To receive items you have bid on, you must 'say collect' to the
auctioneer.
To cancel items from the auction house, you must use the
'cancel' command while in the auction house.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/autodispose.c
keywords: dispose, get
header: Topic:  Auto Dispose
syntax: autodispose <item|-item>

The autodispose command will let you set a list of items you wish to
automatically dispose any time you pick them up via the get all command.
This will not affect things which you get manually, are given to you,
etc, these items will only be disposed when you pick them up via
get all.

Examples:
    autodispose gloves

The above line will automatically dispose ALL of the gloves that you
attempt to pick up via get all.

    autodispose -gloves

Adding a - before the item name will remove it from the list.

Typing autodispose without any arguments will display your current list.

NOTE: items which were accidentally disposed of via this mechanic will
not be reimbursed!  Use at your own risk!


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/autohp.c
keywords: mortal, hp, combat
aliases: 
short: Toggles the hpbar on and off
header: Topic: Autohp

  SYNTAX:  autohp

The autohp command gives you the option of turning on and off the
hp bar, which appears after every combat round and most other times
that you take damage (e.g., falling down a big hole onto a rather
large, sharp, rusty spike).
Note: You can pass an argument '1' to this command to cause your
      HP to show every round regardless.  Please don't do this.
      (Because it's unnecessary CPU usage.)


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/autokeep.c
keywords: mortal, basic, i, mudeq, keep, eq, equipment
short: Automatically Keep Equipment
header: Topic: Equipment

  Syntax:  autokeep [on|off|<slot>|slots]

This command allows you to toggle whether you automatically keep
items in certain slots when you wear or wield them.

Using 'on' you will automatically keep items in all slots.
Using 'off' you will no longer automatically keep any items.
Using 'slots' will list all available slots.
Using <slot> will toggle that individual slot on or off.
Using no arguments will show you your current settings.


