--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/botcheck.c
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
 Command: botcheck <person/SHOW/key>
 e.g.:  botcheck rastafan
        botcheck ab+5!y

So, it's the middle of the night, and someone has stolen your kill
for the eleventieth time and is not responding to tells.  You're
almost certain they're botting but no wizards are around (amirite?)
This is your chance to have it checked yourself.  You can 'botcheck'
another player.  If they FAIL that botcheck, you can be sure the
wizards have noticed and will intervene.  However, if they are just
ignoring you and not botting, you'll get the talking to for being
impatient and/or annoying.

If you've been botchecked, you can make it go away by typing the
keyword that's been shown to you using 'botcheck <keyword>'
Someone cannot be botchecked when already botchecked.
You cannot botcheck more often than every 20 minutes.
If botchecked, you have 15 minutes to do something about it.
If you cannot read your keyword, you can 'botcheck SHOW' to have it
displayed again, differently.

The keyword has no uppercase characters in it, even if it looks like it.

You should really try to validate, through tells or other means, if a
person really isn't around before using this command.  Although the
command is anonymous to the receiver, you are logged for the wizards.
A botcheck is received as a 'tell' and does show up in your tell history.

--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/brief.c
keywords: mortal, movement, look, glance
aliases: 
short: Adjusts your brief/mapping exploration settings
header: Topic: Brief

  SYNTAX:  brief

This command allows you to choose what you see as you walk around 3Kingdoms.
There are two facets to this command, brief and mapping...

Brief   : Controls whether you see the Short (one-liner) or Long (verbose)
on/off    descriptions of rooms.

Mapping : Controls whether or not you see the cardinal minimap.  This map
yes/no    is displayed in the right side of your screen and starts out as
          a basic display of exits from your current room.  As you gain
          more skill in cartography ('help adventuring.cartography'), this
          automated minimap becomes much more useful, showing surrounding
          rooms, exits and even monsters and other players in the vicinity.
          You should also check out 'help lineofsight' for more creamy
          mapping goodness.

To adjust your pesonal settings, choose one of the following...
  'brief'          - displays your current brief settings
  'brief on yes'   - brief mode on, yes show the mapping
  'brief off yes'  - brief mode off, yes show the mapping
  'brief on no'    - brief mode on, no don't show the mapping
  'brief off no'   - brief mode off, no don't show the mapping

Note: Regardless of your brief setting, you can still always look at
      the long description of a room via the 'look' command.  Whether
      or not you see the minimap at this time will depend on your
      mapping setting being yes or no.

Note: Regardless of your brief setting, monsters, players and objects
      in the room will still be displayed.

Note: Be careful when exploring new areas in brief mode, you will most
      likely miss many interesting (and potentially dangerous) things.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/bug.c
keywords: mortal, reporting, bugfree
aliases: bugs
short: Log bugs within a wizards' areas or with an item
header: Topic: Bug

  SYNTAX: bug <descriptive text> 
           bug <item>: <descriptive text>

Used to report a suspected or known bug within an area/room,  
monster, item, or thing that you're either carrying or is in
the room with you.  The command will log the descriptive text
you supply to the appropriate wizard.
Please ensure you provide enough information so that the wizard
can figure out what the bug is.

PLEASE NOTE:
  If you are reporting a bug regarding an item, a colon must  
  be placed after the item you are reporting.                 
                                                              
Examples:
  When reporting a bug located within an area/room,           
      bug It wont let me go south from here.                  

  When reporting a bug involving an item in your inventory,   
      bug bag: The long desc says this is a bag but it        
               does not id to bag.                            


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/bugfree.c
keywords: mortal, bug, reporting
aliases: 
short: In a bugged dark room with no exits?  No problem!
header: Topic: Bugfree

  SYNTAX:  bugfree

If you ever find yourself stuck in a dark room with no exits,
it is most likely bugged.  Not all no-exit rooms are bugged, but
you will probably know it if you see it.  Before you go calling
for a wizard to help you, please try the 'bugfree' command.  If
indeed the room is bugged, you will be transported to the login
room and a report will be written for the wizards to address.

If you are not transported, the room isn't bugged, and you have
to find another way to exit the room.


