--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/cassist.c
keywords: mortal, basic
aliases: 
short: Assist a player in combat
header: Command: cassist

   Syntax:	cassist <+/-player|+everyone|+clear|+show>

This command causes you to automatically assist someone in combat.  This
could occur upon your arrival to the room, when your friend engages in
combat or when your friend is attacked.
You can assist as many players as you like, or even everyone.  It's
encouraged that you only use this on your party members because some
people (most) probably don't want your help otherwise.

Example:  cassist bob,joe,fred
           cassist +larry (I forgot to add larry)
           cassist -bob   (I forgot I hate bob)
           cassist +clear  (I screwed up, lemme start again)
           cassist +show   (krikey, I can't remmeber who I'm helping.)
           cassist john    (screw it, I'm only helping john, nix the rest)

