file: /cmds/mortal/drop.c
keywords: mortal, basic, remove, keep, unkeep, get
aliases: 
short: Drop an object
header: Topic: Drop

  SYNTAX:  drop <object> OR drop all

  The 'drop' command allows you to drop most items from your inventory.
Noted exceptions include guild objects, cursed items, and several other
items that were coded as 'undroppable' because the wizard did not want
an item passed along for one reason or another.  These items have no
value and will destruct when you quit the game.

The drop command will also accept 'all' as an argument, and this
will cause you to attempt to drop all unkept items in your inventory.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/dungeons.c
keywords: dungeons
aliases: instances
short: Which dungeons am I 'saved' to?
header: Command : Dungeons

Syntax: dungeons [player/directive]

This command allows you to see all the dungeons that you are currently
saved to, the boot you're saved until (inclusive), when you're allowed
to clear your ID (if at all), and the ID of the dungeon and any players
(currently online) that are saved with you.  

You will not be able to enter a dungeon area with players that are saved
to a different ID.  Similarly no one can enter your dungeon if they have
a different ID.  The only way to get the same dungeon ID as another
player is to party with them.  (Partying with players saved to various
different dungeon IDs will have interesting results...)

You can check the dungeons your party mates are saved to with:
  dungeons <player>
You can leave a dungeon group with:
  dungeons clear <name or ID/all>

Example output:
=========================================================================
------------------------- Boot Number:  873 -----------------------------
=========================================================================
- Dungeon                   : Boot# Can Reset   ID/With
- -------                   : ----- ---------   -------
- Smurfland                 :   873 1H 47M 42S  [15]
- Chess Board               :   873 1H 19M 42S  [16]
- Death Taco                :   874 now         [8]
=========================================================================


Indicating that I'm saved to Smurfland through boot 873, unless I choose
To leave that dungeon ID earlier, which I can do in 1 hour and 47 minutes.
My dungeon ID for Smurfs is 15, and there's no other players online right
now that are saved with me.
My lock on Death Taco won't expire for a few more boots if I desire, but
I could leave that dungeon ID now if I wanted, if perhaps I was going
to party with someone else in that area who is also already saved.

See also: scaler

