file: /cmds/mortal/earmuffs.c
keywords: mortal, shout, communication, shoutblock
aliases: earmuff
short: Block shouts from a certain level up to your level
header: Topic: Earmuffs

  SYNTAX:  earmuffs OR earmuffs <number>

The 'earmuffs' command with no argument will show you the
current level at which your earmuffs are set.  Earmuffs allow
you to block some of the shouting that occurs on the mud.

The argument that may be added to the 'earmuffs' command is
the level of players up to which you will ignore the shouts.

You are only able to earmuff anybody at or below your level.

Type 'vaf muffs1' to learn more about how to block higher level people


