file: /cmds/mortal/emote.c
keywords: mortal, soul, feelings
aliases: 
short: Express yourself with emotes
header: Typo: emote

  SYNTAX:  emote <message>
            OR :<message>
            OR : <message>  (note the space between)

The 'emote' command, which may be abbreviated by a single colon
as shown above, may be used to relate feelings and perform 'soul
commands' that are not already part of the mud.  Everybody in
the room will be able to see your emotes.

For example, typing in:
    emote looks at you and shivers in fright.

will display to the room:
   <Your name> looks at you and shivers in fright.

You can also emote just to yourself... for whatever reason, by adding
the word 'SELF' to the front, such as: emote SELF is lonely.
And only you would see: '<yourname> is lonely.'
You should seek help if you use this option, or stop botting.


