--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/fbchat.c
keywords: mortal, communication, feedback
aliases: 
short: Feedback Chat
header: Topic: Feedback Chat

  SYNTAX: fbchat <message>

The 'fbchat' command lets you access a mudwide chatline when wizards
indicate that they are interested in soliciting feedback regarding a
particular topic.  This line is *only* active when a wizard is actively
soliciting feedback.

It is strongly encouraged to stay on the topic as described by the wizard.
Any attempt to bring up another topic is only distracting, no matter how
important you think it is.  If it's a critical bug, please contact the
wizard staff directly.

Feedback Line Commands:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    fbchat <-t>         : display the topic of discussion
    fbchat <who|-w>     : show whos listening to the feedback channel
    fbchat <block|-b>   : toggle blocking of the feedback channel
    fbchat <history|-h> : history of the feedback channel

Wizard Feedback Line Commands:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    fbchat -start <topic> : Start feedback discussion on the specified topic
    fbchat -stop [msg]    : Stop feedback with the optional goodbye message
    fbchat -force <msg>   : Force a comment through, even if no topic is set

TITLED Feedback Line Commands:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    fbchat -ban <who> <reason> : Ban a player from the feedback line
    fbchat -unban <who>        : Remove a ban from a player
    fbchat -whobanned          : List all banned players online


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/finger.c
keywords: mortal, basic, who, who2, nwho, mwho, swho, character, players
aliases: 
short:  Get more information about a character
header: Topic: Finger

  SYNTAX:  finger <person>
           finger <level>
           finger

Without an argument this will show every character online in this realm, their
level, guild, gender, and pk status.  With arguments, it will only show the
character specified or characters of the specified level.

  Example: finger barnaby  (shows information about 'Barnaby')
  Example: finger 49       (shows all characters of level 49 logged in)

You can also use the alternative 'qf' command for a condensed version.

You will notice that, if applicable, the finger command also provides
you with information about character and their existence across realms.
Additionally, you are able to access finger information about a specific
character on a specific realm by using the following format:

  Example: finger barnaby@3k  (shows info about 'Barnaby' on realm 3k)


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/fixmob.c
keywords: mortal, bug, reporting, bugfree
aliases: 
short: Unkillable Mob? No Problem!
header: Topic: Fixmob

  SYNTAX:  fixmob <mob>

If you encounter a mob that won't die because it appears to be bugged out,
try this command on it before you notify a wizard. Sometimes they get
stuck in a half-dead state and this command should fix that. If it
fails to fix the issue, then please alert a wizard manually.

Usage of this command is logged for future debugging and to ensure it is
not used in a manner that is inappropriate. If anyone is found using this
for reasons other than stated, there will be consequences.


