aliases:
short: The Flappers Chatline
header: Topic:  Flapping Chat

  SYNTAX:  flapchat <message>

The 'flapchat' command will allow you to talk on the mudwide
chatline for general chatter.  It's blocked more often than shout and is
generally intended for idle chatter and interesting topics.  This is
not a gripe line or a personal pedestal.  Respect the conversation and
please do not overuse it.
You can 'flapchat off' to never see it again.
You can also 'flapchat on' when you realize how much you miss it.
The content of this chat line should be rated 'PG' as per normal rules.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/flee.c
keywords: mortal, basic, miscellaneous
aliases: 
short:  Run out of the room in a random direction
header: Topic: Flee

  SYNTAX: flee

  This will cause you to flee out of the room in a random direction.
  If you have your 'wimpydir' set, it will use that direction first.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/follow.c
keywords: mortal, unfollow, lose, followers, following, party, basic
aliases: 
short: Follow the leader
header: Topic: Follow

  SYNTAX:  follow <person>

This command starts you following someone until either:
   a) They lose you
   b) You stop following them

NOTE: If you have problems with this command PLEASE mail Rastafan.

***Things to keep in mind:

You cannot follow people through 'teleports'.  Some wizards code exits
that in effect 'teleport' you from one place to the next, although it may
seem like you just walked there, you didn't.  So, if ever you find that
you couldn't follow someone somewhere, it's probably because they were
teleported through the exit.


