--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/i.c
keywords: mortal, basic, look, mi, eq
aliases: inventory
short: See what you are carrying
header: Command: i (inventory)

   Syntax:   i <reverse|kept|unkept>

The inventory command will show you everything you are carrying.
Additionally, if you are wielding or wearing any items, this will
be indicated next to the item.  The last line will show you how much
of a burden your equipment is to you. Using the <reverse> argument
will flip the order things are listed (useful if you have a small
screen or it otherwise scrolls by too fast). Using <kept> or <unkept>
arguments will show you only items kept or unkept, respectively.

NOTE: You cannot see your inventory if you are in a dark room.

   Example:

>i
 # Item
-- -------------------------------------------------------------
 1 A bright shiny button that says: Kiss me! I finished the 3K Pub Crawl!.
 1 A message checker.
 1 Brief Combat Tool.
 1 A link tell.
 1 Mywho lister.
 1 A gold wedding ring (worn).
500 coins (weightless)
You are unencumbered.
>


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/ibrief.c
keywords: mortal, miscellaneous, combat, attack
aliases: 
short: Item Briefer
header: Topic: Item Brief

  SYNTAX:  ibrief [<arg> | all [on|off] | needed <arg> | [on|off] <arg>]

     Item Briefing
 Commands:
  ibrief              - Lists briefed items in your inventory.
  ibrief <arg>        - Toggles brief on <arg> in your inventory.
  ibrief on <arg>     - Toggles brief on for <arg> in your inventory.
  ibrief off <arg>    - Toggles brief off for <arg> in your inventory.
  ibrief all [on|off] - Toggles brief on/off for your entire inventory.
  ibrief needed <arg> - Logs an item that should allow briefing.

 ibrief will, on an item by item basis, block some/all messages 
 from the item to reduce your combat spam. Each item must be
 individually coded for this to work. If you find an item that does
 not support briefing but should, use 'ibrief needed <arg>' to tag
 the item for wizards to add the functionality to it.

 Note: Ibrief affects what *you* see and will not generally affect
       what is displayed to the room/others.

 Also note, dropping an item will reset its brief setting.

--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/idea.c
keywords: mortal, bug, typo, reporting
aliases: 
short: Submit an idea
header: Command: Idea

   Syntax:    idea <descriptive text>
               idea <item>: <descriptive text>

Used to suggest an idea for a room, or an item located within 
your inventory.  An item may be any weapon, armour, or object 
you can carry.  The command will log the descriptive text you 
supply to the appropriate wizard.  Please ensure you provide  
enough information so that the wizard can determine the full  
concept of your idea.

PLEASE NOTE:
  If you are suggesting an idea regarding an item, a colon    
  must be placed after the item in question.                  

   Example

  When suggesting an idea for a room:                         
    idea Would be cool if I could write my name in the dust.  

  When suggesting an idea involving an item in your inventory:
    idea sword 2: Could you add ansi to the damage emotes?    

   See also:  bug, typo

