--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/keep.c
keywords: mortal, basic, unkeep, give, drop
aliases: 
short: Keep an item
header: Command: Keep

   Syntax:	keep <item|all [equip | bound]>

Keep allows you to mark an item for keeping in your inventory.
This is especially handy when you are carrying a large number of
items and wish to perhaps sell off the majority to Cancer.  Using this
command you can 'keep' the items that you don't want to sell and then
'sell all' without fear of having to buy back your stuff.

You may choose to use the 'all' option to mark all items for
keeping.  You can also 'keep all equip', which will mark all
worn armours, as well as your wielded weapon as kept.

You may also 'keep all bound' to keep all equipment that is
currently bound to you.


   Example
      keep sword


