--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/medals.c
keywords: medals, medal
aliases: 
short: List awarded medals
header: Command: Medals
syntax: medals || medals <id> || medals <id> <who> || medals <block/show>
    There are many avenues in which a person may obtain a medal
  throughout the realms.  Some may be awarded through mundane
  tasks, such as killing an enemy of a certain denizen of 3K.
  Others may be awarded through quest like tasks; and yet some
  may be given without realizing it.

  Commands:
   medals          - Shows you the medals you've achieved and your
                     achievement point total
   medals show [s] - Shows all public medals and the point total, with
                     optional [s]earch string that matches owner, realm,
                     name, or id of the medal
   medals missing  - Show the medals you do NOT have
   medals top      - Show the top medal earning players
   medals <id>     - Show the specifics of a given medal
   medals <id> <p> - Show medal <id> to player <p> in your room

    The rewards for obtaining a medal may be purely status
  enhancing.  It may however allow you to enter certain other
  areas of the realms by gaining the trust of those who award
  you with them.  Point being; you will have to figure out the
  rewards on your own.  Happy hunting!

    Note: 'medals block' will turn on/off your availability to
  view other's medals.  This will cut down on attempted spam.

    Note: You may only examine medals you possess or are shown.
  You may alternatively peruse the archives in Pinnacle and lookup
  awards gained by fellow adventurers.  Please note, there are two
  classifications.  Public and private.  You may only view private
  medals if you have gained possession of one, and only see it in
  someone else's lookup if you have both earned it.


