--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/mywho.c
keywords: mortal, addwho, ansiwho, checkwho, diswho, mywho2, mywhosync, mysoul
aliases:
short: Using your Mywho Lister
header: Mywho lister
syntax: mywho [-active]

The mywho command will show you a sorted list of the people you have added
to your mywho list that are online.  It will list their levels, their
genders, whether or not they are idle or linkdead, and to what guild each
belongs.  It's a good way to keep track of your online friends!  Use this
command in conjunction with the other commands listed below.

Options: -online    : Do not list the linkdead players.
         -unidle    : Do not List the idle players.
         -active    : List only the players both online and unidle
                      less than 5 minutes.

You may have up to 50 names on your mywho.
Type 'vaf mywho' to learn how to add 25 more.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/mywho2.c
keywords: mortal, addwho, ansiwho, checkwho, diswho, mywho, mywhosync, mysoul
aliases:
short: Another mywho listing command
header:  Topic:  Mywho2
syntax: mywho2

The mywho2 command will show you a sorted list of the people you have
added to your mywho list.  It will list the player's name, and when
they were last were online or how long they have been online.  It's a
good way to keep track of your online friends!  Use this function in
conjunction with 'mywho'.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/mywhosync.c
keywords: mortal, addwho, ansiwho, checkwho, diswho, mywho, mywho2, mysoul
aliases:
short: Synchronizing your mywho with your linktell
syntax: mywhosync

The mywhosync command will allow you to add people that are currently
online and on your mywho list to your linktell list.  You may only add
as many names as your linktell allows, even if there are more listed
online on your mywho.

Players who are link dead or idle for more than 10 min will not be
added to the link.


