--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/pvote.c
keywords: mortal, polls, poll
aliases: polls
short: Check or vote on player polls
header: Topic: Voting on Polls

  SYNTAX:  pvote
           pvote <type> <option>
           pvote <history_types>

The 'pvote' command with no argument will show you what
polls are open for voting.

A valid <type> is the first letter of the poll you are voting on.
(eg. Q for quickpolls, B for bootpolls)  A valid <option> is a
letter A though E, depending on how many options were registered
for the poll.

Example: pvote q c

This will vote for option C on a quickpoll.

Use the ANSI variable "poll_headers" to change the color.
(see 'help aset')

The following <history_types> are available to query recent polls:

pvote -h  OR pvote hist  - The most recent poll of all types
pvote -qh OR pvote qhist - Recent quickpolls (up to 5)
pvote -bh OR pvote bhist - Recent bootpolls  (up to 5)

Polls may be registered for a fee with Rikken in Pinnacle.
NOTE: You must be level 5+ to use the polling system.

