--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/read.c
keywords: mortal, look, examine, basic
aliases: reading
short: Read something
header: Command: Read

   SYNTAX:	read <object|sign|board>

Every character may read signs, boards, messages written on walls, etc.
You may also attempt to read any object you come across.  Some objects,
such as fine weapons, may have inscriptions which may be read.  Reading
signs and objects is a good way to learn additional information and
possibly find a few clues that you may have otherwise missed.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/reboot.c
keywords: mortal, reboot, time, mudlag, miscellaneous
aliases: 
short:  How long has the mud been up / When is reboot
header: Topic: Uptime

  SYNTAX:  uptime [#]

The 'uptime' command will provide you some information on the status of
the mud as far as player statistics are concerned.

The uptime command tells you:

    1) How long the mud has been up this current reboot
    2) When the next reboot is (modified for your timezone)
    3) The length of the next reboot
    4) Other crap

Feel free to use 'uptime2' for a quick, condensed version of the data

Please note that emergency situations that occur might change the time
and/or length of the next reboot.  These situations are rare, but can occur.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/redo.c
keywords: mortal, history, communication
aliases: 
short: Redo - Redirect a typoed line
header: Command: Redo
syntax: redo <wrongcmd> <newcmd>

Occasionally, a player will mistype the verb when typing out
a nice long chat. Needless to say, it's a pain in the neck to
go ahead and retype the whole thing. This command exists for
just such situations.  If you mistype a command or chatline you can
use this command to redo the command without retyping the entire thing.
To do so just type 'redo <oldcmd> <rightcmd>' and it will reissue
the last command that matches 'oldcmd' but as the new right command.
e.g.  shouut What guild should I join?
      redo shouut shout
That will change your typoed 'shouut' to 'shout'.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/reflex.c
keywords: mortal, skills, alias, panic, repeat
aliases:
short: Reflex triggers skill
header: Command: reflex
syntax: See Below

    reflex add <hp|sp|gp1|gp2> <number | %> <command>   -Adds a reflex.
    reflex <remove | delete> <hp/sp/gp1/gp2> <number|%> -Deletes a reflex.
    reflex <start | unpause | enable>      -Starts all reflexes.
    reflex <stop | pause | disable>        -Stops all reflexes.
    reflex <clear | reset>                 -Removes all reflexes.
    reflex clear <hp|sp|gp1|gp2>           -Removes corresponding reflexes.
    reflex combat [on | off]               -Toggles combat only mode.

Allows you to review and configure your reflex actions.

E.G.     reflex add hp 50% say Ack, only half HP left!
         reflex add hp <50% tell kikipopo I'm dying you smeghead!
         reflex remove sp 350

NOTE:     <number | %> can begin with a '>' or '<' for greater/less than.

If you set your reflex but then somehow lose the skill (i.e. it came
from an item), you may reflex clear to delete it (and stop it).

