file: /cmds/mortal/remotevaf.c
keywords: vaf
aliases: 
short: Remote commands to alter VAF perks
header: Command: Remotevaf

This command allows you to perform VAF perk related functions from afar.
Obviously you can only work with VAF perks which you have selected.
Type 'help vaf' for more information on how to get these perks.

 Formats: remotevaf <command>
          remotevaf <command> <argument> (if applicable)

 setplan              : Edits a plan to appear below your finger information
 setalign title       : Sets your alignment title to 'title'
 setalign clear       : Clears your alignment title
 setalign default     : Sets your alignment title to what it really should be
 settitle title       : Sets your main title to 'title'
 settitle clear       : Clears your main title'
 setpretitle pretitle : Sets your pretitle to 'pretitle'
 setpretitle clear    : Clears your pretitle'
 setwname color       : Sets your who name to be colored 'color'
 setdesc desc         : Sets your description to 'desc' (supports ansi!)
 setdesc clear        : Clears your description
 setpose pose         : Sets your custom pose message to 'pose'
 untrain skill        : Untrains a single 'skill'
 unquest quest        : Clears your completed quest 'quest'
 getchecker           : Retrieves your lost remote board checker
 nopk                 : Early-aborts a VAF choice of pkboot


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/repeat.c
keywords: mortal, basic, miscellaneous, panic, reflex
aliases: 
short:  Set or show repeat actions
header: Topic: Repeat

  SYNTAX: repeat <when>/<action>/[dur]/[phase]/[notify]

The 'repeat' command allows you to set up an action to occur every
round, every combat round, and/or every non-combat round.
The following options are available:
 action : what command you would like to repeat
 when   : 'always', 'combat', or 'nocombat'
 dur    : for how many rounds, 0 means forever
 phase  : 0 = at the beginning of your round
          1 = at the end of your round
          2 = between your guild's automations but before attacking
          3 = between your guild's automations but after your attacks
          (you will want to tweak this depending on how your guild reacts)
 notify : A message you want displayed when it expires, only valid if
          you've provided a duration

Examples:
 Turn it off:
  repeat combat/off  -- off in combat
  repeat off  -- everything off

 In combat, always cast a spell after my guild has had its first chance to
 intercede in the round:
  repeat combat/cast death face at goblin/0/2

 I'm a cat...:
  repeat always/lick self/10/0/0/You are now clean.

 Combat has ended, repeat 1 time at the beginning of the first round that
 there is no combat:
  repeat nocombat/guildchat I'm not fighting, my bot broke./1/0


