--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/save.c
keywords: mortal, score, miscellaneous
aliases: 
short: How to have 'score' be there again for you when you relog
header: Topic: Save

  SYNTAX:  save

  The save command takes your stats (which include your strength,
dexterity, experience, age, quest info you used, etc.) and places
them all on the mud hard drive for future reference. This future
reference is usually when you log on again the next day.
  Fortunately for you, you are saved automaticly every 15 minutes,
when you quit and (unfortunately) when you die (no way to weasel out
of that unpleasant experience).

  For those who wonder why this command even exists. Well, if the mud was
pink and there were no wizzes or random force of nature then this command
would have been obsolete and I wouldn't have told you about all this.
  But life is not as such, and accidents (and "accidents") do happen that
cause the mud to crash unexpectingly causing all information of you
between the last save to the present moment to be completely lost and
there will be no proof that you actually did kill cancer.
  So sometimes it is wise to follow the advice I give when I start coding:
             "Save now, and save often!"


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/say.c
keywords: mortal, sayhist, communication, whisper, tell, shout, gossip
aliases: 
short: How to talk to someone completely FREE!!
header: Command: Say
::::::::::::::::::::::
    Topic: say
::::::::::::::::::::::

  Syntax:  say <message>

This wonderful command allows you to speak absolutely FREE! Not
a single spell point is lost. "How is this possible?" you might
ask (that's the first thing I asked when someone told me it's
possible). Well, there is a catch. 
The catch is that you can talk to only the people that are in the
same room with you.
"That's not too bad." you might say. There is also a second catch.
Second catch is that everyone that is in the room with you can hear
you too. So if you are in center of town, don't say things like
"I think *CENSORED*" because someone might hear you, and if you want
them to hear you, then you might as well use shout.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/sayhist.c
keywords: mortal, say, communication, tellhist, shouthist, soulhist, history
aliases: 
short: What to do when you are getting senile?
header: Command: Sayhist
::::::::::::::::::::::
    Topic: sayhist
::::::::::::::::::::::

  Syntax:  sayhist

So you are alone in the room with your mudlover. They come close
to you. They say something and just then one of the bored wizzes
wants to show how cool he is by spamming everyone with a giant dest
message. You try to reach for the scrollbar, and they you discover
that it's broken, what do you do?
Fortunately, we have a solution, type 'sayhist' and see the 20
recent messages that were said by you, or someone else in the room
you are. You can look at it as your own personnal secretary.


