souls for you to play with (or update old ones). How do you keep up
with the hundreds of souls available on the mud?
It's all in 'soulnew' which gives you a list of the most recently
changed souls and new souls that are currently in the game and that you
are capable of doing.
No more will you be the last to find out and you can impress your
mudmate by a barrage of new amusing and heart endearing souls.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/south.c
keywords: mortal, movement
aliases: 
short: How to move south
header: Command: South
::::::::::::::::::::::
    Topic: south
::::::::::::::::::::::

  Syntax:  south

You hear a growl from the north (every seasoned adventurer knows that the
most fierce monsters live in the north parts). You, on the other hand,
are not in the mood for fierce and therefore you want to go in the
opposite direction, south.
If the room has these words in the description:
'Obvious exits: south,...'
Then indeed you can run for your life by typing 'south' (the same goes
for rooms that in the short descriptions it says 'A room (s,...)')
A little ascii picture to illustrate:
                               nw n ne
                                 \|/
                                w-*-e
                                 /|\
                               sw(S)se


