You enter a room and it says: 'for a good time, head southeast'.
Everyone likes a good time, and now you can be just like everyone
by typing 'southeast' or in the abbriviated form 'se'.
If the room has these words in the description:
'Obvious exits: southeast,...'
Then it's time to put on those party hats by typing 'southeast' (the same
goes for rooms that in the short descriptions it says 'A room (se,...)')
A little ascii picture to illustrate:
                               nw n ne
                                 \|/
                                w-*-e
                                 /|\
                               sw S(SE)


