--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/tell.c
keywords: mortal, tellhist, tellb, communication, say, whisper, shout, gossip
aliases: 
short: Talking to your friends from afar
header: Topic: Tell

  Syntax: tell <player> <message>

The 'ask' and 'tell' commands are identical, but are both installed
for your grammatical convenience.

These commands let you send a message to a single player on the mud,
whether they are in the room or not.

There is no cost for this.  To reply automatically to the last person
who 'told' you something, use the 'reply' or 'respond' command.

Note: Tells will reach a person, even if they are in a different realm
To send a tell to a person in a specific realm, use the @ symbol.
For example: 'tell barnaby@3k2 hey there'

You cannot tell to anybody that is tellblocking you.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/tellb.c
keywords: mortal, tell, tellhist, communication, shoutblock, trs
aliases: 
short:  Tellblock a certain person's annoying tells
header: Topic: Tellb

  SYNTAX: tellb OR tellb <player name>

The 'tellb' command will allow you to block the incoming tells
from someone you want absolutely nothing to do with.

With no argument, the command will list all the people you are
tellblocking.  With the argument as a player's name, you will
tellblock that person.  Typing 'tellb <that person>' again will
remove them from the tellblock list.

Type 'help vaf' to learn more about how to tellblock all at once.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/tellhist.c
keywords: mortal, tell, tellb, communication, sayhist, shouthist, soulhist, history
aliases: tellhistory
short:  Shows the last 10 tells you have received
header: Topic: Tellhist
syntax: tellhist

The 'tellhist' command is a very handy device.  This command
will show you the last 16 things that people have told to you,
just in case you missed in the scroll.

  'tellhist' will return your latest tells, up to 16
  'tellhist #' will return your latest # tells

Type 'vaf tellhis' to learn how to get a quadruple-sized tellhist, 64 tells!


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/time.c
keywords: mortal, uptime, mudlag, miscellaneous
aliases: 
short:  What time is it?
header: Topic: Time

  SYNTAX: time

The 'time' command, useful in case you forget your watch and don't have 
a clock handy, defaults to Eastern Standard Time.  If you live in 
another timezone, you can adjust the displayed time by going to the 3K 
modifications office (up from the Pinnacle Shop), and following the 
instructions there to set the TIMEZONE variable.

EXAMPLE:
    ____________________________________________________ 
   (____________________________________________________)
    |                                                  | 
    | Marble Time/Date (EST): Fri Aug 21 15:46:15 1998 | 
    | Your Zone's Time (PST):            12:46:15 PM   | 
    |__________________________________________________| 
   (____________________________________________________)



--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/townportal.c
keywords: mortal, hail, dmap, citymap, newbieland, newbie
aliases: 
short:  Town Portal
header: Topic: Townportal

  SYNTAX:  townportal [check|newb|pinc|stop]

By typing 'townportal', you will begin the process of 
creating a portal back to town, or, if less than level 5, back to
newbieland entrance.  You can also specify which location you would 
prefer, and you can also stop the process using 'townportal stop'.
The process takes several rounds to complete, and this duration increases
as you level up.  Any movement cancels the process.  You can see the
time remaining until you can cast townportal using 'townportal check'.
This command is only available to players level 30 or lower.


