file: /cmds/mortal/tskill.c
keywords: mortal, cost, levels, rcost, stats, skills
aliases: tskill
short: Training others' skills
header: Command: Tskill
:::::::::::::::::::::::
    Topic: tskill
hicyan::::::::::::::::::::::::

  Syntax: tskill <who> <which>

This allows you to train someone's skill as long as they have requested
it via the advance command.  The exact syntax of what you need to type
will be shown to you when the requesting player attempts to advance
the skill in your presence.
Note: You only have 30 seconds from the initial request to begin
      the training, otherwise the request expires.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/typo.c
keywords: mortal, reporting, idea, bug
aliases: typos
short:  Phrase a comment in the form of a question
header: Topic: Typo

  SYNTAX: typo <descriptive text>
           typo <item>: <descriptive text> 

Used to report a typo in a room, or on an item located within 
your inventory.  An item may be any weapon, armour, or object 
you can carry.  The command will log the descriptive text you 
supply to the appropriate wizard.  Please ensure you provide  
enough information so that the wizard can figure out what the 
typo is.

PLEASE NOTE:
  If you are reporting a typo regarding an item, a colon must 
  be placed after the item you are reporting.                 
                                                              
Examples:
  When reporting a typo located within a room,                
      typo The chandelier in line one is misspelled.           

  When reporting a typo involving an item in your inventory,  
      typo sword 2: In the desc, firey should say fiery.      


