file: /cmds/mortal/unfollow.c
keywords: mortal, follow, followers, lose, basic, party
aliases: 
short:  Stop following someone
header: Topic: Unfollow

  SYNTAX:  unfollow <person|ALL>

The 'unfollow' command will stop you from following whomever you
are following.  This does assume you are indeed following someone
at the time. 'ALL' will, suprisingly, stop following everyone.


--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/unkeep.c
keywords: mortal, basic, keep, give, drop
aliases: 
short: Unkeep an item
header: Command: Unkeep

   Syntax:	unkeep <item|all [equip | bound]>

The 'unkeep' command is the opposite of the 'keep' command.
It will allow you to unmark an item previously marked as kept using the
'keep' command. This will then allow you to drop or give the item.

You may choose to use the 'unkeep all' option to mark all items for
unkeeping. You can also 'unkeep all equip', which will mark all
kept worn armours as well as your wielded weapon as unkept.

You may also 'unkeep all bound' to unkeep all kept equipment that is
currently bound to you.


   Example
      unkeep sword


