--------------------
file: /cmds/mortal/uptime.c
keywords: mortal, reboot, time, mudlag, miscellaneous
aliases: 
short:  How long has the mud been up / When is reboot
header: Topic: Uptime

  SYNTAX:  uptime [#]

The 'uptime' command will provide you some information on the status of
the mud as far as player statistics are concerned.

The uptime command tells you:

    1) How long the mud has been up this current reboot
    2) When the next reboot is (modified for your timezone)
    3) The length of the next reboot
    4) Other crap

Feel free to use 'uptime2' for a quick, condensed version of the data

Please note that emergency situations that occur might change the time
and/or length of the next reboot.  These situations are rare, but can occur.


