file: /cmds/himort/hm.c
keywords: highmortal, hmpowers, communication
aliases: hmline
short: The High Mortal line
header: Hm - the High Mortal line

SYNTAX:  hm <command>|<message>

The High Mortal line is a communication line for those players who have
achieved the High Mortal status. Like all other public lines, swearing 
is not allowed on this line.

The following is a list of supplementary commands and toggles for the 
high mortal line:

COMMAND:           NOTES:
~~~~~~~~           ~~~~~~

hm who             Lists the players listening to the HM line.
hm history         Lists the last messages on the HM line.
hm on              Subscribe to the HM line.
hm off             Unsubscribe the HM line.
hm block           Toggle blocking of the HM line.


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/hmblast.c
keywords: highmortal, hm
aliases:
short: Highmortal Blast
header: hmblast

Syntax: hmblast [damage type/'check']

The 'hmblast' highmortal command will allow you to unleash destructive 
energies into a foe.  Wisdom and knowledge of the three kingdoms allows 
the wielder of this power to summon any damage type they wish and 
the damage done increases in relation to the player's abilities.
If you use the 'check' argument it will tell you when you can next
use the power.

Note: Use of this power inhibits the use of hmheal.

Damage Types: edged, blunt, fire, ice, mind, electric, energy, acid, 
              poison, radiation.


