--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/hmmuff.c
keywords: highmortal, rules, punishment, earmuffs, shoutblock, trs, tellblock
short: Earmuff high-level shouts
header: Hmmuff - earmuff high-level shouts

SYNTAX:  hmmuff <level>

The 'hmmuff' command is used for High Mortal characters wishing to earmuff
shouts that are higher than normal players can earmuff. Each level that
a High Mortal wishes to earmuff will cost a certain amount of spell points
depending on the level. Wizard shouts can also be earmuffed with this command,
but at a higher cost. The maximum wizard level that can be earmuffed is 750.
You cannot use hmmuffs until you are higher than level 49.


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/hmrejuvenate.c
keywords: highmortal, hm
short: Rejuvenate the player, purging death sickness.
header: hmrejuvenate

Syntax: hmrejuvenate <whom> 

This allows you to purge the dreaded death sickness from yourself 
or at higher levels, others.  With no argument supplied, you will attempt 
to rejuvenate yourself.

Note:  The ability to hmrejuvenate is available at the rank of Seeker.
       It can be utilized once per boot.


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/hmsever.c
keywords: highmortal, hm, quit
aliases: 
short: Unconditional Quit
header: hmsever

Syntax: hmsever

The 'hmsever' highmortal command will allow you to quit from any
room on the mud, except for the infamous no-quit areas.  Use
this command wisely, for it can only be utilized once per day.

Note:  This command can be used to escape combat.
Note:  This command can be performed by all high mortals.


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/hmsever2.c
keywords: highmortal, hm, quit
aliases: 
short: Unconditional Quit With Item Save
header: hmsever2

Syntax: hmsever2

The 'hmsever2' highmortal command will allow you to quit from any
room on the mud, except for the infamous no-quit areas.  Use
this command wisely, for it can only be utilized once per week.
When you log back in after this, all your equipment will return to you.


Note:  This command can be used to escape combat.
Note:  This command can be performed by Oracles.


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/hmshield.c
keywords: highmortal, hm
aliases: 
short: Shield Yourself
header: hmshield

Syntax: hmshield

This will engulf you in a protective shield that bleeds off 75% of all
incoming damage.  The duration is damage based and increases with your
level and QP total.


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/hmsummon.c
keywords: highmortal, hm
short: Summon forth a destroyer/protector.
header: hmsummon

Syntax: hmsummon <creature> [tank]

This ability lets you summon in a powerful ally to battle.  You can
summon one of three creatures to help you.  They are:
  Hydra - Attacks with fangs and poison.
  Mime - Causes insanity with non-amusing antics.
  Droid    - Has two shoulder-mounted lasers and rockets.
Each one is similar in power but with their own attack types.
You can summon only one of these creatures every four hours.
With the optional 'tank' argument the creature will tank for you.

Note:  The ability to hmsummon is available at the rank of Prophet.


