--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/summon.c
keywords: hmpowers, highmortal
short: Summon a player
header: Summon - summon a player

SYNTAX:  summon <player>

The 'summon' command can only be used by High Mortal characters. This
command allows player A to 'summon' player B to his present location.
Player B must respond 'yes' for this command to work. This command will
only work if both players are located in a MUD owned area.


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/title.c
keywords: highmortal, pretitle, describe 
short: Change your title
header: Title - change your title

 SYNTAX:  title <newtitle>

The 'title' command can only be used by High Mortal characters. This
command will allow the character to change his/her title to one of
their own choosing, within the realm of good taste.  Obscene or offensive
titles are not permitted and can result in loss of levels or deletion.
Note: The syntax 'title clear' will give you a blank title.

Additional note: If your title starts with a comma or an apostrophe,
it will directly follow your name without a preceding space.  e.g:

   > title , the leaping gnome

will display your name as:

   Joeschmoe, the leaping gnome

WARNING: ANSI is not allowed in any title nor are special characters.


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/unfrog.c
keywords: highmortal, hmpowers, frog
short: Remove a Frog or Goat curse
header: Unfrog - remove a Frog or Goat curse

SYNTAX: unfrog <player>

The 'unfrog' command is a High Mortal power that allows a player to remove
the effects of certain curses. Curses that may be removed are The Curse of
the Frog and The Curse of the Goat.


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/whoinvis.c
keywords: who, mywho, players, finger, hmpowers, highmortal, whovis
short: Make yourself 'who'-invisible
header: Whoinvis - make yourself 'who'-invisible

SYNTAX:  whoinvis

The 'whoinvis' command allows a High Mortal player to make themselves
'invisible' to other players with fewer QP than you on certain lists. The lists
that are affected are the various who commands, and players (<guild>).


--------------------
file: /cmds/himort/whovis.c
keywords: hmpowers, highmortal, whoinvis, who, players, finger
short: Make yourself 'who'-visible
header: Whovis - make yourself 'who'-visible

SYNTAX: whovis

The 'whovis' command will allow a High Mortal character to become visible
again on the who lists. This command counters the whoinvis command.


